AKURE – In preparation for the bye-election into the vacant seat of Akure North/Akure South federal constituency at the House of Representatives, the major political parties in the state, All Progressives Congress(APC) and Peoples Democratic Party (PDP) have adopted the indirect mode of primary election to determine who become the standard-bearers of the parties. PDP has disclosed that 350 delegates would determine the fate of the seven aspirants who had obtained and submitted the interest form of the party. PDP’s state Publicity Secretary, Kennedy Peretei, stated that all the seven aspirants would participate in the party’s primary, noting that none of them withdrew from the race. Delta: Keston Okoro Dumps PDP For APC Presidency 2023: I Will Contest If PDP Zones Ticket To South… In a statement, Peretei said: “About 350 delegates from the two local governments are expected at the venue to elect the candidate. The election will be a seamless and peaceful exercise.” He, therefore, expressed optimism that the PDP would win the major election, saying “We have been consulting Akure people to vote for the PDP as a party that can deliver for them and not disappoints the people,” Peretei added. APC would hold its primary election on Tuesday with 715 delegates to decide the fate of eight aspirants who obtained and submitted interest forms of the party.